THe lighted Candles upon he Altar, admoniſh us, (according to S. Luke,) to be ready, in imitation

of the wiſe Virgins, with the Oyl of Good works in our Lamps, of True Faith, and to expect at the pronouncing theſe ſacred and operative words of Conſecration, the real and true ſubſtantial preſence of that our Divine and Heavenly Spouſe;
                              Mat. 5.16 who requires the light of our Good Works ſo to ſhine before Men, as thereby they may be moved to glorifie the Father who is in Heaven.
